    <p>
      Girls are ahead of boys and the highest-performing local authority areas for attainment 8 are concentrated in London and the south, while the majority of the lowest-performing areas are in the north and midlands.
    </p>

    <p>
      The GCSE and equivalent results continue to vary between different race groups. Within each of these broader race groupings, the minor race groups show further variability:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-bullet">
      <li>Chinese pupils are the highest achieving group.</li>
      <li> Pupils from a black background are the lowest performing group although black pupils are progressing above the national average.</li>
      <li>Pupils from an Asian background are performing above the national average.</li>
      <li>Pupils from a mixed background are also performing above the national level.</li>
      <li>Within the minor race groupings, Indian pupils are performing well above the national average </li>
      <li>Gypsy/Roma pupils are the lowest performers.</li>
